OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776250558
OL,3,CHow doing your washing at weekends
OL,4,Ccould get you a discount on your
OL,5,Celectricity
OL,7,FOver the summer months, British
OL,8,Fhouseholds and businesses could be
OL,9,Foffered free or discounted electricity
OL,10,Ffor completing their household chores
OL,11,Fon the weekend, in an attempt to
OL,12,Ftackle periods of excess electricity
OL,13,Fsupply.
OL,15,FThe National Energy System Operator
OL,16,F(Neso) is rewarding consumers who
OL,17,Fincrease their electricity use when
OL,18,Fthere is an oversupply of energy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
