CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776250558
OL,3,CHow doing your washing at weekends
OL,4,Ccould get you a discount on your
OL,5,Celectricity
OL,7,FIn the summertime, the days are
OL,8,Flonger, and temperatures are warmer,
OL,9,Fwhich means consumers do not require
OL,10,Fas much electricity to heat their
OL,11,Fhomes or switch on lights.
OL,13,FOverall, the demand for electricity is
OL,14,Flower than in the winter months, but
OL,15,Fthe generation of electricity through
OL,16,Fwind and solar power remains high.
OL,18,FAs a result, the amount of electricity
OL,19,Fgenerated can exceed demand.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31706
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776250558
OL,3,CHow doing your washing at weekends
OL,4,Ccould get you a discount on your
OL,5,Celectricity
OL,7,F"Our analysis shows that low demand is
OL,8,Fincreasingly driven by weather
OL,9,Fpatterns ` most notably solar
OL,10,Fphotovoltaic (PV) generation ` rather
OL,11,Fthan underlying consumer behaviour,"
OL,12,FNeso says.
OL,14,F"This has a range of consequences,
OL,15,Fincluding when the seasonal minimum is
OL,16,Flikely to occur and what time of day.
OL,18,F"This, in turn, affects the volume and
OL,19,Ftype of actions we must take to
OL,20,Fbalance supply, demand and system
OL,21,Fneeds."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
