OL,3,CHow doing your washing at weekends
OL,4,Ccould get you a discount on your
OL,5,Celectricity
OL,7,FIt comes as National Gas have said gas
OL,8,Fstocks in Britain are set to be
OL,9,Fsufficient enough to meet demand from
OL,10,Fhouseholds and businesses this summer,
OL,11,Fdespite prices surging amid the
OL,12,Fconflict in the Middle East.
OL,14,FNational Gas stressed that British
OL,15,Fdemand for gas will be primarily met
OL,16,Fby supplies extracted from the UK
OL,17,FContinental Shelf and imports from
OL,18,FNorway.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,318,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31713
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1776250558
OL,3,CHow doing your washing at weekends
OL,4,Ccould get you a discount on your
OL,5,Celectricity
OL,7,FAround 86% of the total gas supply
OL,8,F(25.3 bcm) is expected to come from
OL,9,Fthese sources.
OL,11,FThe organisation said it expects this
OL,12,Fvolume to be enough to exceed forecast
OL,13,Fdemand from Great Britain and gas
OL,14,Fexported to Ireland.
OL,16,FIt added that around 5% of the total
OL,17,Fsupply will also come from flexible
OL,18,Fgas storage, and around 9% of the
OL,19,Fsupply will come from LNG imports.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
